title: PML-N’s Sultan Haider Ali Khan wins PP-20 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Sultan Haider Ali Khan of Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-20 Chakwal-I by securing 52,450 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was independent candidate Ali Nasir Khan who bagged 43,250 votes.
Voters’ turn-out remained 60.99 %.
